  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">WWSOSA Coordination Hub</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1.                Creating physical and virtual networking spaces for us to work together and strengthen impact
2.	Providing opportunities to develop joint advocacy campaigns to influence those in authority
3.	Providing links to training and online resources to help members learn and grow, and be more effective
4.	Operating as a hub for coordination, communications and resource mobilisation &#x2013; helping members to connect to each other, find partners for joint actions and sometimes raise funds together
5.	Documenting stories to celebrate what members are doing, and we are doing together in the faith sector, to learn from each other and influence others to inspire them to transform.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">If organisations and individuals working together from a faith perspective to end sexual  and gender based violence (SGBV), then we envisage survivors of SGBV organising themselves for mutual support  and faith sector advocacy to end SGBV ,leading to a united and effective faith response to ending sexual  and gender -based violence in South Africa,leading to a transformed ,just and reconciled communities where the lives of women, boys,  and girls are no longer shattered by sexual and gender based violence</narrative>
  </description>
